<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megaselia subnitida" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnitida">Megaselia subnitida</taxonomicName>
runs to couplet 104, together with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megaselia lucifrons" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucifrons">Megaselia lucifrons</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
